column2: If a country *has a medium or low electricity consumption (less than 56 billion kWh)*, what is the chance (or probability) that it won at least one gold medal in the last Olympics? Give your best guess.
If a country *has a high electricity consumption (more than 56 billion kWh)*, what is the chance (or probability) that it won at least one gold medal in the last Olympics? Give your best guess.
What is the percentage of countries *having a high electricity consumption (more than 56 billion kWh)*? Give your best guess.

If a country *has a medium or low electricity consumption per person (less than 4200kWh)*, what is the chance (or probability) that it won at least one gold medal in the last Olympics? Give your best guess.
If a country *has a high electricity consumption per person (more than 4200kWh)*, what is the chance (or probability) that it won at least one gold medal in the last Olympics? Give your best  guess.
What is the percentage of countries *having a high electricity consumption per person (more than 4200kWh)*? Give your best  guess.
What is the percentage of countries *having won at least one gold medal in the last Olympics*? Give your best guess.
